<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B76164778E8FF00265DFDC0" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B76164778E8FF00265DFDC0" blockId="6.[136,1452,158,977]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B76164778E8FF0026CAFF75" bold="true" box="[189,400,194,220]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
—The species is referred as a variety of 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7616477B0EFF0023B6FF74" authority="Linnaeus (1785: 1145)" authorityName="Linnaeus (1785:" authorityPageNumber="1145" authorityYear="1145" box="[859,1260,194,221]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ciliaris">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7616477B0EFF0024BEFF75" box="[859,996,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Sida ciliaris</emphasis>
Linnaeus (1785: 1145)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7616477D4DFF002658FEA8" author="Hochreutiner, B. P. G." pageId="6" pageNumber="111" pagination="10 - 59" refId="ref19159" refString="Hochreutiner, B. P. G. (1902) Malvaceae novae vel minus cognitae. Annuaire du Conservatoire et du Jardin Botaniques de Geneve 6: 10 - 59." type="journal article" year="1902">Hochreutiner (1902: 35)</bibRefCitation>
. However, we adopt the 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7616477A4AFF242594FEA9" author="Rodrigo, A." box="[543,718,230,256]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" pagination="81 - 212" refId="ref20258" refString="Rodrigo, A. del P. (1944) Las especies argentinas y uruguayas del genero Sida (Malvaceae). Revista del Museo de La Plata (Nueva Serie), Seccion Botanica 6: 81 - 212." type="journal article" year="1944">Rodrigo (1944)</bibRefCitation>
species concept, which separates 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7616477C06FF252388FEA9" authorityName="A. Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1825" box="[1107,1234,230,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="anomala">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7616477C06FF252388FEA9" box="[1107,1234,230,257]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">S. anomala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7616477D4FFF2522DCFEA9" authorityName="Linnaeus (1785:" authorityYear="1145" box="[1306,1414,230,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ciliaris">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7616477D4FFF2522DCFEA9" box="[1306,1414,230,257]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">S. ciliaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by linear leaf blades, flowers with 
<quantity id="C01E9B680B76164779A1FEC82577FE8C" box="[500,557,266,293]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
in diameter, and mericarps with large irregular prominences (muricate) at the dorsal face (vs. suborbicular or cuneate-truncate leaves, flowers with 
<quantity id="C01E9B680B7616477BDEFEEC248DFEE0" box="[907,983,302,329]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" unit="cm" value="1.5">1.5 cm</quantity>
in diameter, and mericarps fine reticulate, with short spinose prominences only at the lateral angles). After analyzing herbarium materials, we believe that these diagnostic characters are sufficient to separate the two species. 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7616477B01FEB42358FE39" author="Rodrigo, A." box="[852,1026,374,400]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" pagination="81 - 212" refId="ref20258" refString="Rodrigo, A. del P. (1944) Las especies argentinas y uruguayas del genero Sida (Malvaceae). Revista del Museo de La Plata (Nueva Serie), Seccion Botanica 6: 81 - 212." type="journal article" year="1944">Rodrigo (1944)</bibRefCitation>
states that 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7616477CD4FEB5225AFE39" authorityName="A. Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1825" box="[1153,1280,374,401]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="anomala">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7616477CD4FEB5225AFE39" box="[1153,1280,374,401]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">S. anomala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has erect habit and 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B76164778EDFE59267EFE1D" authorityName="Linnaeus (1785:" authorityYear="1145" box="[184,292,410,437]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ciliaris">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B76164778EDFE59267EFE1D" box="[184,292,410,437]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">S. ciliaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
decumbent or semidecumbent habit in the field. However, we also observed individuals of 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7616477D78FE5922F1FE1D" authorityName="A. Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1825" box="[1325,1451,410,437]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="anomala">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7616477D78FE5922F1FE1D" box="[1325,1451,410,437]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">S. anomala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with decumbent or semidecumbent habit. Therefore its habit does not serve as a diagnostic character. The species can be distinguished from 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B76164779EAFE202537FE55" box="[447,621,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B76164779EAFE202533FE55" authorityName="Rodrigo" authorityYear="1937" box="[447,617,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="paradoxa">Sida paradoxa</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
also from section 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7616477B1CFE2024BFFE55" box="[841,997,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Malacroideae</emphasis>
(
<tableCitation id="4A6403360B7616477BA2FE202314FE55" box="[1015,1102,482,508]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,224,340,364]" captionTargetBox="[144,1440,425,1289]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Sections of Sida with species occurring in Rio Grande do Sul state, and their diagnostic features, according to Fryxell (1985) and Krapovickas (2003)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" tableUuid="539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39">Table 1</tableCitation>
), by linear leaf blades (rarely linear-lanceolate), serrate in the upper half; flowers 
<quantity id="C01E9B680B7616477A85FDC42452FD88" box="[720,776,518,545]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
in diameter; fruits with 7–8 mericarps (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7616477C9CFDC4223CFD89" box="[1225,1382,518,544]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1920,1942]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,187,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-25@4.[190,1398,187,1893]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–F. Sida anomala. A. Flower. B. Branch with flowers buds and leaves. C. Schizocarp. D. Branch leaves and stipules. E. Adaxial surface of leaf. F. Abaxial surface of leaf. G–L. Sida cerradoensis. G. Flower. H. Schizocarps and flower. I. Adaxial surface of leaf. J. Abaxial surface of leaf. K. Sulcate petiole. L. Schizocarp. M–Q. Sida confusa. M. Abaxial surface of leaf. N. Adaxial surface of leaf. O. Flower. P. Branch with schizocarp and leaves. Q. Peduncle and immature schizocarp. Photographs by Martin Grings and Marcio Verdi (O)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415489" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415489/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Figures 1A–F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7616477D27FDC422F9FD89" box="[1394,1443,518,544]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[136,229,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-54@26.[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14. Mericarps. A. Sida anomala. B. Sida confusa. C. Sida farroupilhensis. D. Sida glaziovii. E. Sida cerradoensis. F. Sida cordifolia. G. Sida dubia. H. Sida linifolia. I. Sida lonchitis. J. Sida nemorensis. K. Sida paradoxa. L. Sida planicaulis. M. Sida potentilloides.N. Sida reitzii. O. Sida regnellii. P. Sida rhombifolia.Q. Sida riedelii. R. Sida rubifolia.S. Sida spinosa.T. Sida tuberculata. U. Sida urens. V. Sida viarum. Photographs by Martin Grings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415519" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415519/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">14A</figureCitation>
) (vs. cuneate-truncate leaf blades, subentire, with three teeth at the apex; flowers 
<quantity id="C01E9B680B7616477C65FDE82325FDEC" box="[1072,1151,554,581]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" unit="cm" value="2.5">2.5 cm</quantity>
in diameter; fruits with 5 mericarps).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B76164778E8FDB0237BFCE9" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B76164778E8FDB0237BFCE9" blockId="6.[136,1452,158,977]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B76164778E8FDB025B3FD25" bold="true" box="[189,745,626,652]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Distribution, habitat and conservation status:</emphasis>
—This species is known from 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7616477C18FDB023E5FD25" box="[1101,1215,626,652]" name="Argentina" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7616477C98FDB1226AFD24" box="[1229,1328,627,653]" name="Uruguay" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7616477D6BFDB122FDFD24" box="[1342,1447,627,653]" name="Paraguay" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B76164778DDFD542780FD19" box="[136,218,662,688]" name="Bolivia" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B761647794CFD542607FD19" box="[281,349,662,688]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7616477925FD542509FD19" author="Krapovickas, A." box="[368,595,662,688]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" pagination="209 - 253" refId="ref19538" refString="Krapovickas, A. (2007 b) Las especies de Sida secc. Malacroideae (Malvaceae) del Cono Sur de Sudamerica. Bonplandia 16: 209 - 253. https: // doi. org / 10.30972 / bon. 163 - 4150" type="journal article" year="2007">Krapovickas 2007b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7616477A36FD542416FD19" author="Zuloaga, F. O. &amp; Morrone, O. &amp; Belgrano M. J." box="[611,844,662,688]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" pagination="1 - 3348" refId="ref20813" refString="Zuloaga, F. O., Morrone, O. &amp; Belgrano M. J. (2008) Catalogo de las plantas vasculares del Cono Sur (Argentina, sur de Brasil, Chile, Paraguay y Uruguay). Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 107: 1 - 3348." type="journal article" year="2008">
Zuloaga 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7616477A9FFD55245CFD19" box="[714,774,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7616477B0FFD542314FD19" author="Alverson, W. S. &amp; Michel, L. R. C. de &amp; Dorr, L. J. &amp; Fryxell, P. A. &amp; Krapovickas, A. &amp; Meneses, Q. R. I." box="[858,1102,662,688]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" pagination="786 - 819" refId="ref17710" refString="Alverson, W. S., Michel, L. R. C. de, Dorr, L. J., Fryxell, P. A., Krapovickas, A. &amp; Meneses, Q. R. I. (2014) Malvaceae. In: Jorgensen, P. M., Nee, M. H. &amp; Beck, S. G. (Eds.) Catalogo de las plantas vasculares de Bolivia, Monographs in systematic botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden. Missouri Botanical Garden Press., St. Louis, pp. 786 - 819." type="book chapter" year="2014">
Alverson 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7616477B9EFD552352FD19" box="[971,1032,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7616477C08FD5423ABFD19" author="Bovini, M. G." box="[1117,1265,662,688]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" refId="ref18092" refString="Bovini, M. G. (2020) Sida in Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / jabot / floradobrasil / FB 9206 (accessed 7 July 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bovini 2020</bibRefCitation>
). For 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7616477D6FFD542224FD19" box="[1338,1406,662,688]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Brazil</collectingCountry>
the species is known from 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B76164779DEFD792545FD7D" box="[395,543,698,725]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B7616477A7EFD792456FD7D" box="[555,780,698,725]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso do Sul" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Mato Grosso do Sul</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B7616477B16FD78234EFD7D" box="[835,1044,698,724]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
states (
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7616477C3CFD7823A1FD7D" author="Bovini, M. G." box="[1129,1275,698,724]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" refId="ref18092" refString="Bovini, M. G. (2020) Sida in Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / jabot / floradobrasil / FB 9206 (accessed 7 July 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bovini 2020</bibRefCitation>
). In the latter, it occurs only in southwest region in Park grassland and Shallow soil grassland (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7616477C54FD1C233FFD51" box="[1025,1125,734,760]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1971,1993]" captionTargetBox="[262,1350,253,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[199,1389,190,1947]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution map of Sida anomala, S. cerradoensis, S. confusa, S. cordifolia, S. dubia, S. farroupilhensis and S. lonchitis in Rio Grande do Sul state, Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415491/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Figure 2</figureCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7616477D41FD1C22F6FD51" author="IUCN &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[1300,1452,734,760]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" refId="ref19221" refString="IUCN (2017) Guidelines for using the IUCN red list categories and criteria. Version 13. Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK: Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommitttee. Available from: http: // www. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed 3 November 2019)" type="url" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
criteria, the species is Least Concern (LC) with an Extent of Occurrence (EOO) of 1,095,931.709 Km² and an Area of Occupancy of 220 Km². Furthermore, it does not meet the criterion B(b) and B(c).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
